5000|$|The North-West Passage (1874) is a {{painting}} by John Everett Millais. It depicts an elderly sailor sitting at a desk, with his daughter seated in a stool beside him. He <b>stares</b> <b>out</b> <b>at</b> the viewer, while she reads from a log-book. On the desk is a large chart depicting complex passageways between incompletely charted islands.|$|R
