6000|$|It was at {{the passage}} where Cathy--in her grand plaid silk frock, white trousers, and {{burnished}} shoes--returns to the dreadful Grange; and, [...] "dismally beclouded," [...] Heathcliff <b>stares</b> <b>out</b> <b>at</b> her from his hiding-place. [...] "'He might,'" [...] I read on, [...] "'well skulk behind the settle, at beholding such a bright, graceful damsel enter the house. [...] "Is Heathcliff not here?" [...] she demanded, pulling off her gloves, and displaying fingers wonderfully whitened with doing nothing and staying indoors.'" ...|$|R
